body:
Reference module ports don't work correctly when modules aren't inlined. It causes a failure of the following test:
```systemverilog
module my_mod (
    ref int x
);
    task static check();
       if (x != 15) $stop;
    endtask
endmodule

module t;
   int a = 15;
    my_mod mod (
        .x (a)
    );

    initial begin
       mod.check();
       $write("*-* All Finished *-*\n");
       $finish();
    end
endmodule
```
The problem can be reproduced by compiling the test with a command `verilator --binary path/to/file -fno-inline`.
